# Logging for New Features

When implementing new features, add logging so activity shows up in Reactotron.

## Logger Location

```ts
import { logEvent, logApi, log, logApp } from '../utils/logger';
// or
import { logEvent, logApi, log } from '../../utils/logger';
```

## When to Log

| Scenario | Use | Example |
|----------|-----|---------|
| User clicks / taps | `logEvent` | `logEvent('Screen:ButtonClicked', { button: 'submit' })` |
| API request/response | `logApi` | `logApi('request', endpoint, { method })` |
| API error | `logApi` | `logApi('error', endpoint, { status, detail })` |
| Screen focus / navigation | `logEvent` | `logEvent('Navigation:ScreenFocus', { screen })` |
| App lifecycle | `logApp` | `logApp('ready', { feature: 'xyz' })` |
| General debug | `log` / `info` / `debug` | `log('Feature', 'message', data)` |

## Examples

```ts
// New API service
logApi('request', '/v1/new-endpoint', { method: 'POST' });
// ... fetch ...
logApi('response', '/v1/new-endpoint', { status, duration });

// New screen / user action
logEvent('NewFeature:ActionTaken', { param: value });

// New auth flow
logEvent('Auth:NewFlowStarted');
logEvent('Auth:NewFlowSuccess');
logEvent('Auth:NewFlowError', { error });
```

Logging is dev-only (no-op in production). Add it for key user flows, API calls, and errors.
